==English==

===Etymology===
[[Hindi]] [[गाड़ी]] ''gāṛi'': a wheeled cart, carriage; a car, truck, bus. From the Old Indo-Aryan gāḍḍa- through the [[Prakrit]] gaḍḍi- <ref>McGregor, R.S, ed. ''The Oxford Hindi-English Dictionary'', Oxford university press. 1993</ref>

===Noun===
'''gharry'''
# A wheeled [[cart]] or [[carriage]] (usually horsedrawn).
# South African military slang: a [[jeep]] or small [[truck]] for conveying troops.

